      • getJsonElementFromGameData

        public com.google.gson.JsonElement getJsonElementFromGameData(String jsonField,
                                                     int packIndex,
                                                     int levelIndex)
                                                       throws com.google.gson.JsonIOException,
                                                              com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException,
                                                              ClassCastException
        Convenience method for getting a JsonElement from a specific GameLevelResponse's gameData blob. This assumes that the gameData is of a JSON format.
        Parameters:
        jsonField - the JSON field you wish to get.
        packIndex - the PackResponse index.
        levelIndex - the GameLevelResponse index.
        Returns:
        the JsonElement requested from gameData on a specific level. Returns null if pack or level index are out of bounds or if jsonField doesn't exist.
        Throws:
        com.google.gson.JsonIOException - the json io exception
        com.google.gson.JsonSyntaxException - the json syntax exception
        ClassCastException - the class cast exception
